################### Steps ################### :
Installing dependencies :
You will need Node, the React Native command line interface, Python2, a JDK, and Android Studio.


Node, Python2, JDK
We recommend installing Node and Python2 via Chocolatey, a popular package manager for Windows.
********************
install chocolatey from here
https://chocolatey.org/docs/installation

First, ensure that you are using an administrative cmd (run as admin cmd )
check below section and copy and past
Install with cmd.exe
If you don't see any errors, you are ready to use Chocolatey! Type choco or choco -? now,

********************

Use choco to instal below package
choco install -y nodejs.install python2 jdk8
(I able to install python2 jdk8 successfully but error in nodejs )


********************
install nodejs from below (download and install for windows 10,  64 bit)
https://nodejs.org/en/download/
********************

After installing nodejs you can install React Native CLI now.
The React Native CLI
Node comes with npm, which lets you install the React Native command line interface.

Run the following command in a Command Prompt or shell:
npm install -g react-native-cli

Here your React Native CLI is ready you can launch it from windows menu like cmd ....


Now install below
1. Install Android Studio
2. Install the Android SDK
Both are installed already in my case so go ahead.

Creating a new application
Use the React Native command line interface to generate a new React Native project called "AwesomeProject":
run below cmd in React Native command line interface
react-native init AwesomeProject

This is not necessary if you are integrating React Native into an existing application,
"react-native run-android" cmd  is just one way to run your app - you can also run it directly from within Android Studio

Modifying your app
Now that you have successfully run the app, let's modify it.

Open App.js in your text editor of choice and edit some lines.
Press the R key twice or select Reload from the Developer Menu (Ctrl + M) to see your changes!
That's it!
Congratulations! You've successfully run and modified your first React Native app.

********************
Some error :
if error comes like below then follow this instruction
could not connect to development server on android

OR
If you get a "bridge configuration isn't available" error


Error :
Could not run adb reverse: Command failed: adb -s a858f25a reverse tcp:8081 tcp:8081

Error :
Unable to load scripts from assets index.android.bundle

Solution : https://stackoverflow.com/questions/44446523/unable-to-load-script-from-assets-index-android-bundle-on-windows


Note : this below will  bring dev setting menu : on screen if your app is on foreground :
adb shell input keyevent 82

change in App.js file and run below
C:\Users\HP\AwesomeProject1>react-native bundle --platform android --dev false --entry-file index.js --bundle-output android/app/src/main/assets/index.android.bundle --assets-dest android/app/src/main/res
run below
C:\Users\HP\AwesomeProject1>react-native run-android

